              deletions, and more than 14,000 larger deletions. We show that
              individuals from different populations carry different profiles
              of rare and common variants, and that low-frequency variants show
              substantial geographic differentiation, which is further
              increased by the action of purifying selection. We show that
              evolutionary conservation and coding consequence are key
              determinants of the strength of purifying selection, that
              rare-variant load varies substantially across biological
              pathways, and that each individual contains hundreds of rare
              non-coding variants at conserved sites, such as motif-disrupting
              changes in transcription-factor-binding sites. This resource,
