              than five errors per billion base pairs in single DNA molecules
              from cell populations. This rate is two orders of magnitude lower
              than typical somatic mutation loads, enabling the study of
              somatic mutations in any tissue independently of clonality. We
              used this single-molecule sensitivity to study somatic mutations
